#Input Functions
#Write a program that prints the number of characters in a user's name. 
#Your program should work for different inputs. e.g. any name that you input.

#Results
#Create a variable called my_name and assign it as an input.
#Print the variable but use the function len to count the characters for output.

print("What is your name?")
my_name = input()
print(len(my_name))

#Better code
#Input run first - passed to len function - which then gets printed
#Download Thonny to see how code gets executed.

my_name = input("What is your name? ")
length = len(my_name)
print (length)

print(len(input("What is your name? ")))

